  <!-- ============ INSIDE THE FILM (anatomy) ============ -->
  <section class="anatomy" id="anatomy">
    <div class="sec-head" data-reveal>
      <p class="sec-eyebrow">Inside the film</p>
      <h2 class="sec-title">A pouch is <em>three decisions,</em> laminated together.</h2>
      <p class="sec-lead">What keeps chips crisp for nine months isn't the print — it's the structure behind it. Scroll through the layers we bond for every job.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="anatomy-grid">
      <div class="anatomy-sticky">
        <div class="film-stack" id="filmStack" data-step="1" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="sheet sheet-print"><span class="sheet-label">Print · BOPP / PET</span></div>
          <div class="sheet sheet-barrier"><span class="sheet-label">Barrier · MET-PET / AL</span></div>
          <div class="sheet sheet-seal"><span class="sheet-label">Seal · LLDPE / CPP</span></div>
          <p class="stack-caption">One film. <em>Your structure.</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="anatomy-steps">
        <div class="a-step" data-step="1">
          <p class="a-step-num">01</p>
          <h3>The print carrier</h3>
          <p>Your artwork is reverse-printed in up to eight colours on rotogravure — so the ink sits <b>inside</b> the laminate. It can't scuff, scratch or fade on shelf, no matter how rough the supply chain is.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="a-step" data-step="2">
          <p class="a-step-num">02</p>
          <h3>The barrier core</h3>
          <p>Metallised PET or aluminium foil blocks oxygen, moisture and light. This layer is why roasted, fried and dried products stay fresh for months — and it's specified per product, not per catalogue.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="a-step" data-step="3">
          <p class="a-step-num">03</p>
          <h3>The food-contact seal</h3>
          <p>LLDPE or CPP on the inside — food-grade, heat-sealable, and strong enough to run on high-speed filling lines without splitting a single seam.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="a-step" data-step="4">
          <p class="a-step-num">04</p>
          <h3>Bonded into one film</h3>
          <p>Solvent-less lamination fuses the layers into a single web — then it's slit, pouched and batch-tested in our own QC lab before dispatch. Common structures we run:</p>
          <div class="laminate-chips">
            <span class="laminate-chip">BOPP / MET-PET / PE</span>
            <span class="laminate-chip">PET / AL / LLDPE</span>
            <span class="laminate-chip is-reel">Mono LLDPE — recyclable</span>
            <span class="laminate-chip">CPP / AL / PET</span>
            <span class="laminate-chip">PET / PE</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
